@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Your privacy is our priority";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #808080;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 50px 20px;
            color: #FFFFFF;
            text-align: center;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 48px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        p {
            font-size: 24px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Privacy</h1>
        <p>
            Privacy is a critical concern for StreamWave, and we are committed to protecting our users' personal information and data. We understand that our users trust us with their information, and we take this responsibility seriously.
        </p>
        <p>
            To ensure the privacy and security of our users' data, we have implemented a range of measures and protocols. We use industry-standard encryption technology to protect all user data, including personal information and payment details. We also regularly review and update our security practices to stay up-to-date with the latest threats and vulnerabilities.
        </p>
        <p>
            We only collect and use the minimum amount of user data necessary to provide our service, and we are transparent about our data collection practices. We provide users with clear and concise information about what data we collect, how we use it, and who we share it with.
        </p>
        <p>
            We do not share user data with any third parties for marketing purposes, and we only share user data with third parties in limited circumstances, such as when necessary to provide our service or comply with legal requirements. We ensure that any third parties we work with have appropriate data protection and security measures in place.
        </p>
        <p>
            Users have the right to control and manage their data on StreamWave. Users can access, update, and delete their data at any time through their account settings. They can also contact our support team if they have any questions or concerns about their data.
        </p>
        <p>
            In summary, StreamWave is committed to protecting the privacy and security of our users' personal information and data. We use industry-standard security measures to protect user data, only collect and use the minimum amount of data necessary, and are transparent about our data collection practices. Users have control over their data on StreamWave and can manage it at any time.
        </p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>